\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces The MSS identification strategy as a DAG. Solid arrows show the assumed causal pathway: rainfall ($z$) affects growth ($y_2$), which affects conflict ($y_1$). Dashed arrows show unobserved confounders ($u$) that bias OLS. Identification of $\beta $ requires the $z \to y_2$ arrow (relevance, testable) and the \emph  {absence} of any $z \to y_1$ arrow (exclusion, not directly testable).}}{2}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:dag-mss}{{1}{2}{The MSS identification strategy as a DAG. Solid arrows show the assumed causal pathway: rainfall ($z$) affects growth ($y_2$), which affects conflict ($y_1$). Dashed arrows show unobserved confounders ($u$) that bias OLS. Identification of $\beta $ requires the $z \to y_2$ arrow (relevance, testable) and the \emph {absence} of any $z \to y_1$ arrow (exclusion, not directly testable)}{figure.1}{}}
